主要翻译
 
thank [sb] ▦ vtr (express gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢 gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 感謝  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 对…表示感谢 
 -- The bride graciously thanked the guests at the reception.
 -- 新娘在接待处感谢出席婚礼的亲朋好友，举止雅致大方。
 
thank [sb] for [sth] vtr + prep (express gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 表示感谢 biǎo shì gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 表示感謝  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 道谢 biǎo shì gǎn xiè，dào xiè 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢谢 biǎo shì gǎn xiè，xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝 
 -- Charlene thanked Scott for the flowers.
 -- Mike thanked Jane for helping him with his maths homework.
 -- 查琳感谢斯科特送花给她。// 麦克感谢简帮他完成数学作业。
 
!! thanks interj informal (expression of gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢谢，多谢 xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝  (感叹词)
 -- Thanks!  What a lovely present!
 -- 谢谢你的礼物！
 
thanks npl (gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感激 gǎn jī TC Traditional Chinese 感激  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢 gǎn jī，gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 感謝 
 -- We give thanks for the love of our family.
 -- 我们对家人给予的爱心存感激。
 
thanks npl (acknowledgment)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 致谢 zhì xiè  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 致敬 zhì xiè，zhì jìng TC Traditional Chinese 致敬 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 致意 zhì xiè，zhì yì 
 -- The board would like to offer thanks to our contributors.
 -- 董事会谨向公司的贡献者致谢。

其他翻译
 
thank [sb] for [sth] vtr + prep ironic (blame)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 责备, 责怪  
 -- Who do we have to thank for this mess?

复合形式： 
 
no thank you expr (polite refusal)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不，谢谢 bù，xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 不，謝謝  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不用了，谢谢 xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝 
 
thank God interj (expression of gratitude or relief)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢上帝 gǎn xiè shàng dì TC Traditional Chinese 感謝上帝  
 -- Thank God you're all right!
 -- That stupid show went off the air, thank God.
 
thank God expr (it is fortunate that)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢天谢地 xiè tiān xiè dì TC Traditional Chinese 謝天謝地  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 还好, 幸好 
 -- Thank God you're coming with me – I'd hate to go alone.
 
Thank goodness! interj (relief)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢天谢地！  
 
thank heaven, thank heavens interj (expression of relief)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢天谢地 xiè tiān xiè dì TC Traditional Chinese 謝天謝地  
 
thank heaven, thank heavens expr (it is fortunate that)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢天谢地 xiè tiān xiè dì TC Traditional Chinese 謝天謝地  
 -- Thank heavens the ambulance is here!
 
Thank you interj (gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢谢你 xiè xiè nǐ TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝你  (表示感激)
 -- Thank you!  I liked the gift.
 -- 谢谢你！我喜欢这个礼物。
 
Thank you for interj (gratitude for)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 因为…谢谢你  (感叹词)
 -- Thank you for the box of chocolates.
 -- 谢谢你给的那盒巧克力。
 
Thank you for doing [sth] interj (gratitude for done)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 因为做…谢谢你  (感叹词)
 -- Thank you for helping me with my homework.
 -- 谢谢你帮助我完成作业。
 
thank-you n (expression of gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感激 gǎn jī TC Traditional Chinese 感激  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢 gǎn jī，gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 感謝 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢谢 gǎn jī，xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝 
 -- Don't forget to say your thank-yous before you leave.
 -- 离开前，别忘了说谢谢。
 
thank-you n (message of thanks)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢 gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 感謝  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 致谢 gǎn xiè，zhì xiè 
 -- She sent a thank-you for the wedding gifts.
 -- 她对结婚礼物表示感谢。
 
Thank you all interj (gratitude to a group)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢大家  
 
Thank you both interj (gratitude to two people)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢两位  
 
Thank You For Not Smoking expr written (no-smoking sign)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 请勿吸烟，谢谢 xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝  (禁止吸烟标志)
 
thank you in advance interj formal (expressing a polite request)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 提前感谢您，先说一声谢谢 tí qián gǎn xiè nín，xiān shuō yì shēng xiè xiè  (正式用语)
 
thank you kindly interj (expressing sincere thanks)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 十分感谢 TC Traditional Chinese 十分感謝  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 谢谢 xiè xiè TC Traditional Chinese 謝謝 
 -- Thank you kindly for shoveling the snow from my walkway.
 
Thank you so much interj (Many thanks)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 非常感谢 fēi cháng gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 非常感謝  
 
thank you very much interj (many thanks)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 非常感谢 fēi cháng gǎn xiè TC Traditional Chinese 非常感謝  
 -- Thank you very much; you've been very helpful.
 -- 非常感谢，你给予了我很大的帮助。
 
thank-you note, thank-you letter n (letter expressing gratitude)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 感谢信  
 -- Don't forget to send them a thank-you letter.

在这些条目还发现' thank '：
在英文解释里：
acknowledge - many thanks - merci beaucoup - much obliged - ta - TGIF - Thanks a bunch - Thanks a heap! - thanks a lot - Thanks a million - You rock!
中文：
感谢 - 谢 - 幸亏 - 有劳 - 谢谢 - 非常感谢

标题中含有单词 'thank' 的论坛讨论：

Cantonese: Thank you!

Dear Mr. ... Thank you very much for your kind reply, I truly appreciate it

I appreciate everyone's help. Thank you!

I can't thank you enough

Mandarin, Cantonese: Thank You

Shanghainese: Thank you

Thank you

Thank you for all your help (formal)

Thank you for bearing with me

Thank you for helping us find the internet cafe.

Thank you for the advice, have this bottle of wine for our thanks

Thank you for the birthday gift!

Thank you for the dragon

Thank you for the photos

Thank you for your birthday wishes!

Thank you for your concern.

thank you for your consideration

thank you for your detailed answer

Thank you for your message

Thank you for your quick reply

Thank you for your reply

Thank you for your warm welcome

Thank you very much!

thank you! but you are late

-Thank you for helping me - Absolutely./It's ok.

''Thank you. Please come again.'' - often said to customers

'And I have you to thank for my deliverance?'

'How do we say "Thank you very much, sir"?' asked Donald. :Punctuation

'right' as reply to 'thank you'

'so much as' thank me



